The german dataset contains data about loan applicants (borrower) of a German credit institution from 1994. There are 1,000 observations and 21 variables, of which 13 are categorical and 8 are numeric. Each observation represents one customer. Categorical Variables * checking - Status of existing checking account * history - Credit history of borrower * purpose - Purpose of loan application * savings - Status of savings/bonds account * employ - Current length of employment * status - Marital status and sex * others - Indicate if someone else will be involved in the repayment or is guaranteeing the loan * property - Collateral for loan * otherplans - Type of installment plans the borrower already has * housing - Residential status of borrower * job - Current type of employment * tele - Indicate if phone number is registered under the borrower’s name * foreign - Indicate if the borrower is a foreign worker

Numeric Variables * Default - Specify if the borrower fully repaid their loan * duration - Duration of loan (in months) * amount - Amount of money borrowed (DM) * installment - percentage of amount borrowed that will be charged by a lender to a borrower * residence - Length of time living at current residence (in years, 4 = 4+) * age - age of customer (in years) * cards - Number of existing credits at this bank * liable - Number of people being liable to provide maintenance for
